content:
I think I'll get there around 10 am to beat the crowd. And yeah, their menu does look pretty extensive, so we'll probably take our time deciding.

As for the new place I tried last week, I think what really stood out to me was the unique dishes they had. They had a lot of creative twists on classic brunch items, which was really refreshing. And the atmosphere was really trendy and modern, which was a nice change of pace from the usual breakfast joints. But what really impressed me was the service - our server was super friendly and attentive, and the food came out really quickly. Overall, it was just a really great experience!
